defaultWritten evidence from defaultIAM (Institute of Advanced Motorists)default (WRT 016)default&#xa0;
defaultThe IAM (Institute of Advanced Motorists) directly influences the driving and riding of more than 135,000 UK road users every year (full members, associates and commercial clients).  
default&#xa0;
defaultEstablished in 1956, the IAM is best known for the advanced driving test and the advanced driving course.  The IAM has grown to become the UK’s largest road safety charity, dedicated to raising driving standards, engaging with the road-using public and inf
defaultluencing road safety policy.  IAM Drive and Survive also provides a range of occupational driver training courses to the commercial market.  In January 2007, the IAM Policy and Research division was established to undertake consultation responses, campaign
defaulting and research to assist in the understanding of road safety issues.
default&#xa0;
defaultOur response is laid out below in the paragraph numbers supplied.
