defaultBut, e
defaultxtended periods of snow and ice will almost certainly have 
defaulta high cost associated with it in terms of 
defaultdisruption and lost productivity
default.  
defaultThe UK grinds to a halt at the first fall of snow and that is an unacceptable 
defaultoutcome
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultMore research is needed on the individual and societal costs of bad weather delays. 
default 
defaultUntil loss of earnings, damage to vehicles, cras
defaulthes and loss of output can be fully quantified by research we will not have a clear understanding of the costs and benefits involved
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultAny analysis should include the cost of 
defaultdaily impact on travel, finding alternatives, if available, and the delays and di
defaultsruption caused by cancellations, traffic jams etc
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultCritical functions 
defaultshould be prioritised 
defaultsuch as daily care of the elderly, NHS patients, 
defaultand heat
default and power 
defaultgeneration. Over
default a prolonged period food production and distribution would assume more importa
defaultnce and priority.
default 
